The paper deals with the problem of bias in machine learning applications, which is a common concern in several sub-fields of computer science. The proposed method involves adversarial training, which is a popular technique in the field of deep learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve synthetic data and medical images, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and medical imaging (cs.CR) research. The paper also discusses the problem of dataset bias, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and fairness in machine learning (cs.SI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.SI.
